s. They helped usher in their modern definitions and created the lenses through which we experience and interpret works of art, establishing modern attitudes not just towards sculpture, but towards cultural patrimony in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aModern History. 7aART / European.2bisacsh  aAntonio Canova, Sculpture, Art theory, Display, Reception theory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048557509?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048557509423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048557509/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131903-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DPKb2023